Calculating probability density function of mfcc¶

In [11]:
def gaussian(x, mu, cov):
    pdf = []
    
    for i in range(x.shape[1]):
        x_vector = x[:,i].reshape(1,-1)
        n_constant = (1 / np.power(2 * np.pi, (cov.shape[0])/2)) * np.power(np.linalg.det(cov), -0.5)
        pdf.append(n_constant * np.exp((-0.5) * np.dot(np.dot((x_vector-mu), np.linalg.inv(cov)), (x_vector-mu).T)))

    return np.array(pdf).reshape(-1,)

Viterbi algorithm¶

In [18]:
p_bar_viterbi = np.array(p)
b = np.zeros(p.shape)

for i in range(p.shape[1]-1):
    
    b0, b1 = np.argmax(trans_mat[:,0] * p_bar_viterbi[:,i]), np.argmax(trans_mat[:,1] * p_bar_viterbi[:,i])
    b[0,i+1], b[1,i+1] = b0, b1

    p_bar_viterbi[0,i+1] = trans_mat[b0,0] * p_bar_viterbi[b0,i] * p[0,i+1]
    p_bar_viterbi[1,i+1] = trans_mat[b1,1] * p_bar_viterbi[b1,i] * p[1,i+1]
    p_bar_viterbi[:,i+1] = p_bar_viterbi[:,i+1]/np.sum(p_bar_viterbi[:,i+1])

for i in range(b.shape[1]-1):
    b_prev = int(b[np.argmax(p_bar_viterbi[:, p.shape[1]-1-i]), p.shape[1]-1-i])
    p_bar_viterbi[b_prev, p.shape[1]-1-i-1] = 1
    p_bar_viterbi[1-b_prev, p.shape[1]-1-i-1] = 0

def eigen_decomp(X, num_eigenvectors):
    max_epochs = 1000
    epoch = 0
    eigen_val = []
    eigen_vec = []
    
    for i in range(num_eigenvectors):
        w = np.random.rand(X.shape[0], 1)
        
        for epoch in range(max_epochs):
            w = np.dot(X, w)
            w = w * (1/np.power(np.sum(np.power(w,2)),0.5))
            
        s1 = np.power(np.sum(np.power(np.dot(w.T, X), 2)), 0.5)
        u1 = np.dot(X.T, w) * (1/s1)
        contrib = s1 * np.dot(w, u1.T)
        
        X = X - contrib
        
        eigen_val.append(s1)
        eigen_vec.append(w.reshape(-1,))

    eigen_vec = np.array(eigen_vec)

    return eigen_vec.T, eigen_val

Training a perceptron¶

def logistic(x):
    return 1/(1 + np.exp(-x))
In [33]:
W = np.random.uniform(0, 1, size=4).reshape(-1, 1)
error_plot = []
max_epochs = 100000
epoch = 0
alpha = 0.1

while epoch < max_epochs:
    prediction = logistic(np.dot(W.T, X))
    error = 0.5 * (np.dot((Y - prediction),(Y - prediction).T))**2
    error_plot.append(error)

    delta_W = np.dot(X,((prediction - Y) * prediction * (1 - prediction)).T)
    W = W - alpha * delta_W
    
    epoch += 1

In [40]:
def neural_network(X, Y, max_epochs, learning_rate):
    
    np.random.seed(0)
    W1 = np.random.randn(3,3)
    W2 = np.random.randn(1,4)

    alpha = learning_rate
    
    Y_hat = []
    error_plot = []
    
    epoch = 0
    
    while epoch < max_epochs:
        
        first_layer_output = logistic(np.dot(W1, X))
        first_layer_output = np.concatenate((first_layer_output, np.ones([1, first_layer_output.shape[1]])))
        
        predictions = logistic(np.dot(W2, first_layer_output))
        
        bp_error_output = (predictions - Y) * (predictions * (1 - predictions))
        delta_output = np.dot(bp_error_output, first_layer_output.T)
        W2 = W2 - alpha * delta_output
        
        bp_error_first = np.dot(W2.T, bp_error_output) * (first_layer_output * (1 - first_layer_output))
        delta_first = np.dot(bp_error_first, X.T)[:3,:]
        
        W1 = W1 - alpha * delta_first
        
        error_plot.append(0.5 * np.dot((predictions - Y), (predictions - Y).T))
        
        epoch += 1
        
    return W1, W2, np.array(error_plot).reshape(max_epochs, 1)
